              content:
                '<div style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; font-size: 16px; color:#333;">\n\n  <h1 style="font-size:20px; font-weight:bold;">Late-Night Salted Nuts: Friend or Foe During Menopause?</h1>\n\n  <p>Hey rebel, let\'s talk about your nightly salted nut habit! While nuts are generally a powerhouse snack—packed with healthy fats, proteins, and nutrients—enjoying them salted right before bed might actually be stirring up some trouble, especially during menopause.</p>\n\n  <h2 style="font-size:18px; font-weight:bold; margin-top:20px;">Here\'s What Might Happen:</h2>\n\n  <ul style="font-size:16px;">\n    <li><strong>Sleep Disruption:</strong> Salty snacks increase thirst, causing you to wake up more frequently for water or bathroom breaks. And let\'s face it, menopause already messes with your sleep—no need to add fuel to the fire!</li>\n    <li><strong>Bloating & Water Retention:</strong> Salt makes your body hold onto water, leading to bloating and puffiness—especially frustrating if you\'re already feeling a bit rebellious about your changing body.</li>\n    <li><strong>Blood Pressure Concerns:</strong> Regularly consuming salty snacks at night can gradually raise your blood pressure, increasing heart health risks—something we want to keep in check during menopause.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h2 style="font-size:18px; font-weight:bold; margin-top:20px;">Your Action Step Today:</h2>\n\n  <div style="background-color:#fdf2e9; padding:15px; margin-top:15px; border-radius:5px;">\n    <p><strong>Swap the Salty Habit!</strong> Tonight, challenge yourself to replace salted nuts with a small handful of unsalted almonds or walnuts, or even better—try a tablespoon of almond butter on apple slices. You\'ll still satisfy your craving, get great nutrients, and dodge the salt-induced sleep sabotage.</p>\n  </div>\n\n  <h2 style="font-size:18px; font-weight:bold; margin-top:20px;">Want to Dive Deeper? Here’s Your Rebel Reading List:</h2>\n\n  <ul style="font-size:16px;">\n    <li><strong>Book:</strong> "<em>The Menopause Reset</em>" by Dr. Mindy Pelz – Practical strategies to reclaim your health and vitality.</li>\n    <li><strong>Study:</strong> <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6770596/" target="_blank">Impact of Dietary Salt on Sleep Quality</a> – Research on how salt intake affects sleep.</li>\n    <li><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://www.menopause.org/" target="_blank">North American Menopause Society</a> – Reliable, science-backed menopause resources.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <p>You\'ve always done things your way—now, let\'s harness that rebellious spirit to make menopause your healthiest chapter yet. You\'ve got this!</p>\n\n</div>',
